# Small commits

Prefer multiple small commits over one large commit.

- Each commit should represent **one coherent change** (e.g. “add db init”, “add dragons router”, “wire startup hook”).
- Commit messages should make it easy to understand **what changed and why** when scanning `git log`.
- Avoid mixing unrelated changes (formatting, refactors, features) in a single commit.

